Clarke's Bread is made with 100% local organic flours, water and sea salt.  We use a traditional sourdough method with a long fermentation time, to help with digestibility.  All of our breads are hand shaped, and hearth baked on a scorching hot stone.  We bake our breads dark. This colouring is the caramelization of the natural sugars brought out by the fermentation process.  Try it. You will have a hard time going back to white bread after this. I promise.

post_content:
For years, coffee enthusiasts have been urging restaurants and bars to try harder when it comes to the quality of their coffee, but serving gourmet coffee can be an investment of time and money that doesn’t bear all that much in returns for a business.
Equipment can run up to tens of thousands of dollars, and only a trained barista can reasonably be expected to pull a perfect shot of espresso.
Smart restaurants and bars are getting around some of these barriers by utilizing The Heavenly Grind Collection series machines that are designed to suit every size of location providing a perfect cup of Espresso, Cappuccino, Lattes, Mochaccino, Hot Chocolate, flavoured coffees like French Vanilla and many more all at the push of a button.

post_content:
Hugh's Room, Toronto's beloved acoustic music club, closed its doors suddenly and unexpectedly in January 2017 after 16 years of operation.  

There was an immediate and overwhelming response to this potential loss to the musical community, with substantial coverage  in the local and national media (Toronto Star, Globe & Mail, Toronto Sun, Now, Exclaim, National Post, Jazz-FM, CBC, CTV, Global, insidetoronto.com, WholeNote, and many others).  

Many members of the music community and public have asked how they could help to save or revive their beloved Hugh's Room.

In response, a working group of volunteers assembled and has developed a viable plan for re-opening Hugh's Room as a not-for-profit organization.  The group includes lawyers, business people, accountants, music promoters, publicists, venue operators and members of the community (members are listed below).  Grit Laskin has been named spokesperson for the working group.  

The group has determined that Hugh's Room can clearly sustain itself financially going forward.  With the right infrastructure and community support, the legacy of Hugh's Room can be continued.  Toronto can continue to have a destination venue that presents the genres, variety and high quality of music that Hugh's Room is renowned for across the continent.

What’s the plan?
A new community based not-for-profit organization has incorporated and will open the new club as Hugh's Room Live.



Fundraising goal is $250,000 with the first $30,000 required by February 20,  THIS BENCHMARK HAS BEEN MET. 

Another $45,000 by March 5.  

THIS GOAL HAS BEEN MET ! 

Another $50,00 by April 15

PLEASE DONATE NOW TO HELP US MEET THIS GOAL.


Please show your support and make your donation as early as possible to ensure Hugh's Room can re-open. 

Who is involved ? 
The working group came together informally, in response to the news of Hugh’s Room’s closing.  All are fans of Hugh’s Room, and wanted to explore how it could re‑open as a community‑owned venture. It includes:

Jeremy Darby, owner Canterbury Music Co (recording studio)

Howard Gladstone, businessman, musician, co-founder Toronto City Roots Festival 2004-2010

Jane Harbury, freelance publicist, has worked for Hugh's Room for many years

Brian Iler, lawyer, chair Northwinds Folk Festival (1984/85), engaged with many community initiatives

Grit Laskin, musician, luthier, member Order of Canada, spokesperson for the Hugh's Room working committee

Judith Laskin, retired educator, founding board member CFMA,  director The Woods Music & Dance Camp, past board member Mariposa Folk Festival under Estelle Klein

Brian Litvin, accountant and musician

Franks Saunders, businessman, involved with presentation and production of folk events

Rob Young, advertising executive and musician 


How was the fundraising goal set?

The fundraising goal was established after an analysis of the previous operation. Our conclusion was that the club is financially viable, but operated in a cash deficit position. The fundraising goal is considered adequate to ensure the financial stability of the new club.  Necessary allocations of the funds include: purchasing the assets, securing a lease from the property owner, providing working cash for the operation, and providing a  financial buffer. 

What about financial transparency? 

As a not-for-profit community-based operation, Hugh’s Room for the Performing Arts will release its budgets and financial statements. 


What about people who bought tickets to cancelled shows? 

The working group is acutely aware of the financial fallout from the cancelled shows, for both audience and artists alike.  Patrons contact your credit card company for a refund after the show date has passed.

What about the former employees of the old Hugh's Room? 

The new organization (Hugh's Room for the Performing Arts)  is committed to re-opening the club as soon as possible.  Doing that is the best way to assist employees who have been hurt by the closure. Our plan is to re-hire as many of them as we can, as soon as we can.   Most former employees have expressed interest in returning.  The original general manager Anthony Ferrando is returning.

post_content:
Are you Craving something different?

The question that started the movement more than 4 years ago. We took on the challenge of changing minds to view healthy fast food in a different light; By putting notions of what fast food is currently to the test, we thrive to break barriers by providing a newer ‘healthy’ and a fresher ‘alternative’ to what “fast food” should be. For the last 3 years, our efforts have been focused on making unique creations, each with their own signature identity and distinguished taste.

We did this day in… day out… for 3 years… 

Our creations have brought together complimentary items to make fresh, healthy food that not only taste groovy but also, are rich in vitamins and minerals.  Every single item has been cleverly mixed to enhance each handiwork to provide variety with a unified taste. The various veggies and fruits takes your taste buds on a journey of flavors, making it hard to believe that something this enchanting can also be good for you. The rich colors and sumptuous aromas come together to craft a nourishing, appetizing handiwork for different palates.  Anyone that wants to change their means for the better should do so within the confines of their own beautiful imagination.

post_content:
We invite you to enjoy an authentic meal steeped in the long lived tradition of Ethiopian cuisine. We welcome you to an atmosphere that represents excellence in service and style.

Our menu has both meat and vegetarian/vegan dishes and also gluten-free injer. It's perfect for people who follow different diets but would like to dine together.

Join us for authentic Ethiopian cuisine with food that is flavorful and spicy. We can customize the degree of heat you'd like. The meal is meant to be shared and eaten with your hands as it is served on large platters meant for sharing.

Try our Martini Wednesday to eat great and enjoy a tasty $3.50 martini. We also have coffee roasting session.

Enjoy our Ethiopian coffee ceremony in which coffee is taken through its full life-cycle of preparation. Coffee is roasted until the beans turn chocolate brown, then ground and put in a traditional pot made out of clay and boiled to perfection. Once the grains are set, it is poured out for you to enjoy and savor. 

We also offer ceremony classes so you can re-create this wonderful, unique experience at home.

Ethiopiques Restaurant is perfect for:
REGULAR DINNER: Dine-In, Take Out, Delivery
SPECIAL BOOKING: Private Group Lunch, Catering

post_content:
Cosmic Treats is a fully licensed, kid-friendly vegan restaurant, dessert bar, ice cream parlour and candy shop in the heart of Kensington Market that strives to provide vegans with the food and treats they can’t get anywhere else. We also promise to make omnivores happy by offering great tasting, familiar comfort foods like Spaghetti & Meatballs, All Day Breakfast, and Chick’n Pot Pie that don’t TASTE vegan – they simply taste delicious!

We feature a rotating selection of over 40 flavours of our silky smooth made-in-house, small batch, premium artisanal ice cream made using a cashew nut base. Our ice cream received the Toronto Veggie Award in 2016 &  2017 for “Best Vegan Ice Cream” in Toronto.

The owners of Cosmic Treats, husband and husband team Tim and Elliot, went vegan together in 2001. Since then they have traveled the world looking for the most delicious vegan eats and treats they could find.

When they decided to open Cosmic Treats in October 2015, they tried to bring the most delicious and hard-to-find products, the best of their best recipes, and all the things they loved (vegan food, robots, chocolate everything, toys, cashew ice cream sundaes, the colour orange, science fiction and baked goods) into one place. The kind of place that they would go to as soon as they got off the plane if they were traveling.

At Grasshopper, flavour comes first. That fact that our menu is meat-free is just a bonus.

Our menu offers a broad selection of meatless meals, snacks, sides and fresh juices. We draw inspiration from across the globe and from our own diverse and vibrant city. We are committed to offering an ever changing array of the foods you want to eat.

Our debut menu is set to feature cross-cultural comfort foods like quinoa mac 'n' cheese, burgers, bibimbap, bahn mi and soups. We pride ourselves on cooking to order, from scratch to maximize flavour and freshness.

WHO WE ARE
Our team is passionate about making vegetarian food taste great above all else. As vegetarians we're familiar with Toronto's meatless dining options and we know what's missing. We offer a distinct point of view that is centred around fresh and tasty traditions and adventurous innovations, all offered at an affordable price point.

Join us for lunch or dinner in our casual and cozy contemporary setting, walk in for convenient take-away or call ahead for catering

Our debut menu is set to feature cross-cultural comfort foods like quinoa mac 'n' cheese, burgers, bibimbap, bahn mi and soups. We pride ourselves on cooking to order, from scratch to maximize flavour and freshness.

WHO WE ARE
Our team is passionate about making vegetarian food taste great above all else. As vegetarians we're familiar with Toronto's meatless dining options and we know what's missing. We offer a distinct point of view that is centred around fresh and tasty traditions and adventurous innovations, all offered at an affordable price point.

Join us for lunch or dinner in our casual and cozy contemporary setting, walk in for convenient take-away or call ahead for catering.

Fries: Our fries are hand cut, in-house daily, with the potato skin on.  The potatoes are then fried twice, Belgian style, in 0 trans fat and non hydrogenated vegetable oil, which is also low in saturated fat and cholesterol free.

Cheese: Our cheese curds arrive fresh from Maple Dale Farms, delivered every other day (which maintains their squeakiness).

Traditional Gravy: We make our traditional gravy in-house, everyday, by roasting bones and fresh vegetables, letting them simmer for at least 8 hours, thickening and then seasoning to perfection.

Vegetarian Gravy: We make our vegetarian gravy in-house, everyday, by roasting a variety of fresh vegetables and letting them simmer until ready. Then the gravy is thickened and seasoned to perfection.

Vegan/Gluten-Free: We add a helping of Daiya vegan cheese, the most delicious vegan cheese on the market.  It melts, tastes amazing and doesn't contain dairy, soy, gluten or any nut product.  It is smothered with gravy that is homemade with our vegetarian stock and thickened with cornstarch and nutritional yeast flakes.

Dipping Sauces: Made in-house with real mayonnaise.

The Tabule Family of Restaurants is made up of 4 uniquely designed venues specializing in Middle Eastern Cuisine: Tabule Midtown, Tabule Riverside, Tabule Bayview and the fast casual Souk Tabule.

The first restaurant founded in 2005 by Chef Rony Goraichy and Diana Sideris located in Midtown on Yonge Street, quickly earned its place among the finest Middle Eastern restaurants in Toronto and its popularity rose from there.

2012 saw the launch of Tabule Riverside featuring hip, exotic cocktails and many of the much loved menu items from the original restaurant, like Chef Rony’s famous Falafels, Fattüish Salad and of course their award winning house-made hummus.

In 2016 Souk Tabule, a fast-casual venue became an instant hit in the Canary District followed in 2017 by the newest Bayview Village Shop location.

post_content: Pero Restaurant is as rich and diverse as Eastern African culture. The spectrum of Pero Restaurant cuisine can be said to lie between are two dietary extremes: vegetarianism and carnivorism. The essence of good Eastern African cooking revolves around the appropriate use of aromatic spices. The skill lies in subtle blending of a variety of spices to enhance, rather than overwhelm the basic flavour of a particular dish. Pero's food relies on the spices in which it is cooked, just as Japanese Sushi relies on the freshness of the meat, and Chinese food relies on the various sauces to impart the right flavour and taste. It is interesting to see an Eastern African chef at work, with a palette of spices, gratuitously sprinkling these powders in exact pinches into the dish in front of him. It is these complexities of regional food in Eastern Africa that make it a so very fascinating experience. Pero aims to bring the most traditional dishes from all corners of Eastern Africa, maintain the classic Eritrean recipes and enhance the offering with some signature dishes to reflect the changing food trends in modern Africa.

post_content:
After searching for an Authentic South Indian Restaurant, my wife (Thana) and I (Kumar) realized that Canada was deprived of it. So we decided to open just that, an Authentic South Indian Restaurant with personal touch and care paid to our unbeatable taste and customer service. As I come from a family of Restaurant owners, and I being a business man since 1975 and blessed with an excellent cook, as my wife, we started our venture. Soon our two daughters, who were more than willing to help, joined our team. Our elders have been cooking and mastering the culinary art for many years in which many secret recipes have been created and passed on. With their blessings and knowledge we literally 'exposed' our kitchen and heart to our valued customers since 2003. From the very first day we have never compromised freshness, cleanliness or taste. We take on the challenge of living up to and soaring above the high standards that our customers have set for us. This was possible only after we started making the food ourselves rather than depending on outside commercial cooks...

We would like to take this opportunity to thank all our customers for their support and feedback given throughout our journey. Now, as requested, a dine-in restaurant to match our food, we proudly present to you.  Gurulukshmi

post_content:
We opened April 1, 2011 and have been having fun every day since, right in the heart of Toronto's financial district.  We have loved meeting new customers every day while getting to know our loyal regulars.

The team at Prairie Girl is proud of our incredible cupcakes! We LOVE to talk about how they are made fresh on-site every single day from fresh dairy butter, 70% Dark Belgian Chocolate, real strawberries and tons of other top of the line ingredients!

November 14, 2011 we opened up our second location in the Path.  Located in the concourse level of First Canadian Place, we deliver the same great product, but available at 8am for those early risers, and wonderfully convenient as the cold approaches.

April 26, 2013 We opened our third location in the trendy neighbourhood of Yorkville! Now our cupcakes are conveniently available uptown still served with a smile! 

Because of our commitment to "fresh" each of our stores has it's own kitchen where our favourite products are baked everyday. This means that sometimes we sell out early due to a higher demand than expected. This also means some days we have leftovers and because of our love and dedication to the community in which we work, we give our end-of-day cupcakes to a couple of Second Harvest agencies nearby our stores.

Stay connected with Prairie Girl and you'll get chances to take part in contests and giveaways all the time! :)

Twitter - http://twitter.com/prairiegirlbake
Pinterest - http://pinterest.com/prairiegirlbake
Instagram - http://instagram.com/prairiegirlbakery

Review us on Yelp at: http://www.yelp.ca/biz/prairie-girl-bakery-toronto

Voted Best Bakery in Burlington for the last 6 years, Kelly's Bake Shoppe takes a sweet, honest, and decadent approach to baking. We bring the child-like wonderment into your life with treats backed treats and ice cream too!. We bake with NO artificial colours or flavours and are known as, "The Healthier Bakery that happens to be gluten free, egg-free, lactose-free, dairy-free & peanut-free and vegan." 

We pride ourselves on using the healthiest ingredients and leaving out processed junk and top allergens, so as many people as possible can enjoy desserts, together. Yes... the owners personally live this way too!

Co-Founders, mother & daughter team Kelly Childs and Erinn Weatherbie. Kelly's Bake Shoppe XO opened in December 2012 in downtown Burlington and the rest is history!

post_content:
Indian food is not all the same, but reflects the different conditions spread across this vast land populated by over a billion people. Spices which we use such as coriander, cumin, cloves, cinnamon, cardamom, black pepper, red chili powder, turmeric and mustard are regularly used in Punjabi cuisine. These spices do not dominate the dish, but gently promote the primary ingredient. 

At A1 Sweets, we take great pride in making our dishes and sweets. With many years of experience in the food industry, we have produced sweets and dishes with unique taste. As a 100% vegetarian restaurant, we take pride in providing a great healthy alternative to other restaurants. We offer catering for weddings, birthday parties, family gatherings, religious events, corporate luncheons and more. Stop by for a clean, relaxing dining experience in Scarborough!

post_content:
Bagel Nash is a Canadian owned and operated family business. We opened our doors to our customers in 1997; and have been providing the neighborhood with healthy and delicious food options ever since.

We are proud to say that we currently operate three Bagel Nash locations including our newest location at Gerry Fitzgerald by Dufferin & Steeles , and additionally a French patisserie called Le Delice Fine Cakes. At Le Delice Fine Cakes we offer special occasion cakes (such as birthday cakes, wedding cakes, specialty cakes, and petit fours), as well as hot breakfasts, omelets, wraps, sandwiches and an assortment of other dishes.

Le Delice Fine Cakes is located just next door to Bagel Nash (Bayview Location) and is very well known within the Greater Toronto Area. If you visit this location you will find a seating area between Le Delice Fine Cakes and Bagel Nash, where you can relax, unwind and enjoy our tasty food.

post_content:
Sweet Olenka's is a local family-run business in Toronto.

Founded in 2007, the first Sweet Olenka's location on Lake Shore Blvd. in Etobicoke was the beginning of something truly special.

10 years later, what started began with the one store, has grown into a thriving business with 4 locations.

It is a passion for creating decadent, gourmet desserts that are not only delicious, but also works of art! 

The perfect gift
A box of Olenka's chocolates or truffles is a truly decadent, gourmet gift. From our new Egyptian Themed Gourmet Chocolate Truffles, to our Luxury Edition Assorted Truffles, we have the perfect indulgent gift your loved-one deserves!

For special celebrations
The same care and attention we put into creating our gourmet chocolate is put into making our exquisite cakes.

Choose from a wide variety of sizes and flavours, with an extensive list of decorative options.

Are you vegan or gluten-free?

We've got a cake for you! We offer a substantial selection of delicious vegan and gluten-free cakes.

It is a passion for creating decadent, gourmet desserts that are not only delicious, but also works of art! 

The perfect gift
A box of Olenka's chocolates or truffles is a truly decadent, gourmet gift. From our new Egyptian Themed Gourmet Chocolate Truffles, to our Luxury Edition Assorted Truffles, we have the perfect indulgent gift your loved-one deserves!

For special celebrations
The same care and attention we put into creating our gourmet chocolate is put into making our exquisite cakes.

Choose from a wide variety of sizes and flavours, with an extensive list of decorative options.

Are you vegan or gluten-free?

We've got a cake for you! We offer a substantial selection of delicious vegan and gluten-free cakes.

post_content: Healthy Planet
Final Description:
A lot has changed since 1995. From a small kiosk in a strip mall on Danforth Ave in Toronto, to what Healthy Planet is now, few things have remained the same. The selection, meeting the constant needs of our clients , adapting to changes, providing exceptional customer service, and above all, our commitment to providing the lowest prices to our customers. We believe in keeping prices fair, and building life-long relationships with our customers.

At Healthy Planet, health and wellness is our passion, and we want to share that passion with you by providing with the highest quality vitamins, supplements and remedies for all your lifestyle needs. Healthy Planet's personal goal is to make high quality products readily available and affordable for consumers far and wide. For your convenience, there are several Healthy Planet locations throughout Canada.

post_content:
The Classics Veganized 
December 1st 2017

FAQ Questions 

Can I make a reservation? 
At this time, we are not taking reservations at Mythology. However, if you come by and there is a wait, we are happy to take down your phone number and send you a text as soon as a table opens up. 

Can I order takeout? 
We are not offering a takeout service at this time. However, we do have plans to offer takeout in the future. Be sure to follow us on social media, as we will make an announcement when this service becomes available. 

Do you have a menu online? 
Yes, our menu is posted on our website.  www.mythologydiner.com.

What is your phone number? 
We don’t have one. If you have any questions or comments, please reach out to us at info@mythologydiner.com and we’ll be sure to get back to you. 

Can I leave flyers there? 
No. If you have any additional questions about this, please email us at info@mythologydiner.com.

post_content:
South Indian Vegetarian Restaurant also serving Vegan, Jain, Fusion & Vegetarian Tandoor Cuisine

Our award-winning restaurant has been recognized as the premier Indian establishment at Gerrard community for the year 2002, and we are determined to keep it that way.

We have been offering authentic regional South Indian and North Indian, Vegetarian cuisine here in Toronto since 2001, without letting the clients sacrifice the taste and flavors of fine Indian Cuisine.

For first-timers and South Indian cuisine lovers our soft spongy Idlies, Uthappams and Dosas complimented with authentic home made Sambhar will set a memorable dining experience.

The South Indian Thali is a complete southern satisfaction.

For the adventurous one our Fusion and the Chaats will have them coming for more.
Our Chefs use all their talents and expertise to create a new edge in healthy, fine Indian cuisine of current times.

post_content:
At What A Bagel, we make sure our bagels are fresh and warm all day, every day. What’s our secret? It’s simple - Every bagel is made in-store, straight from our ovens and into your hands. We mix the dough from scratch, boil them, dress them, bake them, and serve them to you all in minutes.

So you think our bagels are good? Then you should definitely try our variety of pastries, danishes, cookies, holiday treats, and delicious challahs. We’ve also expanded our bakery to include a full service brunch restaurant. From omelettes, eggs any style, specialty sandwiches, renowned shakshuka, freshly squeezed juices, cheese blintzes, French toast and pancakes, and fantastic coffee, we certainly have something for everyone. The eatery takes great pride in its heaping portions and its commitment to the freshest and highest quality ingredients that leave our customers satisfied. 

From the moment you enter into our inviting surroundings of What A Bagel's contemporary design and stylishly trendy decor, the mouth-watering scent of onsite freshly baked goods will let you know that you've come to the right place!
Final Description: 11 locations throughout the GTA bringing you 3 generations of bagel making experience. Vegan-friendly bagel options.

Small plates, big flavours. Explore the vast gastronomic range of the Iberian Peninsula with us.

With our devotion to "nose-to-tail" practices and a watchful eye on sustainable and ethical ingredients, Cava remains one of Toronto’s few true destination restaurants.

Designed to quietly accent the ever-evolving cuisine and attentive service, our uncomplicated, charming dining room traditionally seats 56 with bar seating for 10 and patio seating for 10.

Complementing our menu is a deep, yet carefully chosen wine list that offers over 40 wines, cavas and sherries by the glass and more than 200 bottles to enhance the experience. Most recent acknowledgements include being named in the top 10 of Joanne Kates' Top 100 Restaurants of 2014.

post_content:
Harvest Kitchen is our expression of a world of possibility. The way we see it, food is simple. We believe in using fresh, high quality ingredients. We believe in local sourcing (from our friend's farms) whenever possible. We believe in straightforward preparations. We believe in letting fresh, local when possible, straightforward, everyday food speak for itself.

Where can we go to eat the foods we love? Where can we go to eat fresh and tasty everyday meals at reasonable prices? Where can we go that caters to both our eating preferences and those of our friends? Harvest Kitchen is our answer to these questions. The menu was in our minds, the food is how we live.

Harvest Kitchen - where vegetarians bring their meat-eating friends ... and vice versa.

It's some 1700 years since the worldly sage, Mallanga Vatsyayana wrote his epic Indian tale of love... The Kama Sutra. Written in ancient Sanskrit, (for the eyes of the ruling elite only), it's a doctrine dedicated to the celebration of love.
Having studied it from every angle (purely for culinary inspiration!), we realize the words are, in fact, a metaphor for "the love of food". Our culinary team has stayed true to the actual origin of each dish. No stone is left unturned in our quest to provide our guests with a remarkable dining experience.

post_content: At Keeffaa, I cook and serve a fusion of traditional and inspired Ethiopian dishes with much, much love.  It is part of Ethiopian culture to respect and appreciate all aspects of sharing a meal – with this in mind, and to fuel my creativity, I change elements of the menu every day, so the delicious food is fresh and different throughout the week.  I also import green beans directly various regions in Ethiopia, so from time to time you may see me hand roasting green beans from all over Ethiopia, in an Ethiopian style of roasting, right here at the restaurant.  Come and share this nourishing, nurturing food at Keeffaa!

post_content:
Our cuisine is exotic with bold unique taste, and we are proud to serve great dishes with traditional Ethiopian hospitality in our cozy restaurant. At Lalibela it is our pledge to bring you the best of Ethiopia. We have a full bar in our restaurant and have breakfast, lunch, dinner and kids menus. Please call ahead to lounge-in, take-out or carry-out. We also have catering options for events and parties. Free wi-fi is also available!

Our menu consists mainly of vegetarian dishes like our popular vegetarian platter (mild or spicy) which is a combination of splint peas, lentils, chick peas, cabbage, collard greens and other vegetables served with injera, a delicious Ethiopian flatbread. We also have plenty of fantastic meats including lamb, chicken and beef. Try our special Ethiopian coffee, which is served with a traditional ceremony consisting of roasting coffee beans on spot to bring the heavenly aroma for you to enjoy.

Welcome to Mother’s Dumplings, a cozy, welcoming café in the heart of Chinatown! Born in Shenyang, our owner and cook, Zhen, cooks up delicious Northern Chinese style comfort food based on family recipes passed down from generation to generation.

Since opening our doors in June of 2005, Mother’s Dumplings has received praise from numerous publications. We are proud to have been voted Best Chinese Restaurant in Toronto three years in a row! NOW Magazine calls Mother’s Dumplings the “Toronto’s Best $5 Lunch,” saying “this spotless, subterranean, Chinese café specializes in delicious, house-made Chinese dumplings and noodles dishes that are as much a treat for the pocketbook as for the taste buds!” 

We invite you to visit our website for full menus, then stop by our convenient Mother’s Dumplings location on Spadina Avenue today to see what everyone in Toronto is talking about!

OUR SPICY SCALE
Mild – Some dishes are already a bit spicy 
Medium – A little kick 
1 Chili – Nice 
3 Chilis – Thai Medium 
5 Chilis – Watch out 
10 Chilis – Are you sure? 
15 Chilis – Some like it hot 
20 Chilis – May cause stomach upset 
* Indicates dishes that are already spicy.

We’re a community of food lovers and showcase for culinary talent in Toronto. The Dep is a versatile, multi-use space designed to host different kinds of informal food-related events, including Drop-In Dinners, Workshops & Supper Clubs. We also host a lively weekend brunch and offer commercial kitchen space for rent by the hour or the month. We're also the home of Newcomer Kitchen, an innovative new nonprofit social enterprise that provides a venue for Syrian refugee women to cook and sell meals.

MONDAYS 
Cooking classes and workshops  6:30-9:30pm
T.O. cooks share their secrets
  
FRIDAYS
Drop-In Dinners with guest cooks  6pm+
“Open mic night” for culinary talent in Toronto!
 
SATURDAY
The Rusholme Park Supper Club  7:30pm+
Family-style dinner parties with a rotating cast of guest cooks

SAT & SUN
Mazeh - Levantine-inspired Brunch 10am-2:30pm
https://thedepanneur.ca/brunch/

You can easily add your email to our mailing list to receive our weekly update, 
http://www.facebook.com/TheDepanneur/app_100265896690345

or check our Facebook events page to see what's coming up.
http://www.facebook.com/TheDepanneur/events

Learn more about The Dep and how you can get involved on our website:
http://thedepanneur.ca/about/get-involved/

Hope to see you at The Dep!
-LEN

post_content:
Executive Chef Fawzi Kotb brings a sophisticated depth of knowledge to Velouté Bistro & Catering.

A formal private Chef to the royal family of Persian Gulf,  Chef Fawzi mastered his craft and achieved the level of saucier at the “Marriott Hotel Champ-Elysee” Paris, France.  Since coming to Toronto,  Chef Fawzi has continued to excel and succeed at a number of well-established fine dining restaurants. Including, “Centro Grill and Wine Bar” as saucier and contributing creative new development.

As well as “Peppino’s on the beach”, where as executive Chef, Fawzi’s menu rapidly elevated the bistro to one of the top ten restaurants in the city.  His ongoing achievement at Opal Jazz Lounge has won him critical acclaim and a vast loyal following with the years of success and ventures and a high degree of business.

Alise Matos, Owner/Sommelier; brings equal talent and experience to Velouté.

With over 25 years of experience, Alise’s philosophy of service and professionalism has developed to a higher level of service excellence, meeting guests expectations and performance.  Alise is a seasoned event planner who has dedicated extensive time and effort gaining superior knowledge through top restaurants such as Opal Jazz Lounge, The Fifth, Windsor Arms Hotel, Mistura. She is a CAPS member Canadian Association of Professional Sommelier.

Warren has been a fan of barbecue for over twenty years. His influences range from North and South Carolina, Memphis Tennessee to Central Texas. 

When Warren moved to his home on Greenwood Avenue he vowed to bring his love and passion for barbecue to the people. This is where we get our name. 

What you'll find:

* Slow smoked meat sandwiches meals or by the pound (ribs, pulled pork, brisket, chicken, etc)
* Vegetarian-friendly (smoked veggie chili, smoked veggie sandwiches, all-veg side dishes)
* Dine-in and take-out
* Fully licensed, local craft beer, bourbon menu

post_content:
Are you a fan of things delicious?

Do you sit at home wondering where you can be satisfied mouth-ly, stomach-ly and wallet-ly?

Why are you not eating a delicious ROTI right now?

Pam's Caribbean Kitchen offers a great variety of some of the best ingredients a Roti could possibly fit into itself!

Whether you are a vegetarian, meat head, or a spice seeker this place should be a regular stop for you. 

With a "Not-So-Fast-Food" approach to cooking, be ready to sit tight while Pam Singh prepares a taste that will forever make other curry dishes seem bland by comparison.

These rotis are so big, they can last you for 2 meals, or if you eat it in one, YOU WILL NOT EAT FOR DAYS, and will possibly die from palate pleasure.

Check out these great reviews of this wonderful gem of awesomeness:

NOW Magazine
http://www.nowtoronto.com/food/story.cfm?content=164234

YELP
http://www.yelp.ca/biz/pams-caribbean-kitchen-toronto?rpp=40&sort_by=relevance_desc

http://www.torontoplus.ca/toronto/venues/pams-caribbean-kitchen
Final Description:
Are you a fan of things delicious?

Do you sit at home wondering where you can be satisfied mouth-ly, stomach-ly and wallet-ly?

Why are you not eating a delicious ROTI right now?

Pam's Caribbean Kitchen offers a great variety of some of the best ingredients a Roti could possibly fit into itself!

Whether you are a vegetarian, meat head, or a spice seeker this place should be a regular stop for you. 

With a "Not-So-Fast-Food" approach to cooking, be ready to sit tight while Pam Singh prepares a taste that will forever make other curry dishes seem bland by comparison.

These rotis are so big, they can last you for 2 meals, or if you eat it in one, YOU WILL NOT EAT FOR DAYS, and will possibly die from palate pleasure.

post_content:
Snakes & Lattes offers a full menu of food & drink alongside a library full of games. Delivered by savvy baristas, creative bartenders, a talented kitchen staff, and table side service, the staff are available to help guests not only by making suggestions of the menu but also of the games.

A $6 admission provides access to a public library of games, with a diversity from the classics to the modern, from dexterity to trivia, from strategy to party. Whether you come for a thirty-minute Jenga duel or for an afternoon of Eldritch Horror, Snakes & Lattes is happy to host you.

Guests can choose and play any number of the available titles that pique their interest. If picking a game ever feels like a daunting proposition, guests can invite the services of a game guru: mystical, benevolent beings that Snakes & Lattes employs to recommend and teach games.

Beyond the menu and the games libraries, Snakes & Lattes also offers a vast retail selection, whether you prefer to shop in store with the help of our staff or online with free Canadian shipping.

Game on!

post_content:
RICKSHAW BAR is a rustic, casual restaurant, serving exciting small plates and snacks.
Our food is fun, wholesome and most importantly worth sharing.
Like a Rickshaw travelling throughout Asia, our menu explores culinary essences from all over the continent and brings them together in a memorable experience.
Chef Noureen Feerasta explores tastes you would only experience on the streets of South Asia, so join us for a ride and open yourself up to an experience unlike anything you have ever tried in Toronto.

post_title: Crepe Delicious & Froshberg Gelato at Toronto Eaton Centre
post_content:
Healthy eating starts here!
 
Our passion is crepes! Known for our world-class sweet and savoury crepes, we take pride in creating an outstanding crepe experience for you.
 
All of our crepes are made fresh to order, just for you. The crepe itself has only 130 calories and 3.5 grams of fat, and you can fill our crepes with your favourite fresh ingredients for a healthy meal on the go.
 
Serving crepes since 2004, Crepe Delicious is Canada’s largest mall-based creperie and is a leader in the trend towards healthy eating. The Toronto Eaton Centre location also features Froshberg Gelato!

General Information
www.crepedelicious.com
 www.froshberg.com

Bombay To Go is enjoying a fast growing reputation for the excellence of its service and food. Our skilled chefs, blend the finest spices and fresh natural ingredients in selected traditional recipes, as they constantly strive to perfect their art. Their, range of specialities include succulent starters, and mouth- watering meat and vegetarian dishes which reflect the wonderful cultural diversity of India.

Whether you visit our premises or contact us by telephone, you will be greeted in a warm friendly manner and every endeavour will be made to ensure your complete satisfaction.

Should you wish, we would take great pleasure in delivering your meal so that in the comfort of your home, you may enjoy subtle tastes that gently transport you on an exotic journey to the East.

We hope that the food we provide is an enjoyable and enriching experience and that you, by favouring us with your custom, will in turn enrich our lives

post_content:
How spicy do you like it? Check out Butter Chicken Roti on Queen Street for this Indian dish on flatbread filled with curry, and folded up to go. We have six levels of spiciness to the roti that you can pick based on your own tastes. You can customize your roti to a healthier option by adding veggies or meats of your choice to any of the roti. We have a wide range of toppings which includes broccoli, mushroom, green pepper, green peas, chick peas, cauliflower, and much more. Our famous sauce comes fresh on every roti and is made of a combination of garlic, ginger, onion and other sauces. It’s slow cooked for five hours allowing the unique flavors to meld together into the perfect topping for your meal. Butter Chicken Roti is proud to offer something which is unique and customized for every order, made with fresh and high quality, locally produced ingredients.

On the go or in a hurry? Butter Chicken Roti can deliver strait to you, or you can pick up your roti at our shop and enjoy it here. Are you a meat lover? Vegetarian or vegan? We have tons of options to cater everybody’s preferences. We even offer gluten free & halal options. We're a casual eatery that is excited to bring something new to the Toronto food scene, and we would love for you to come join us soon!

On the go or in a hurry? Butter Chicken Roti can deliver strait to you, or you can pick up your roti at our shop and enjoy it here. Are you a meat lover? Vegetarian or vegan? We have tons of options to cater everybody’s preferences. We even offer gluten free & halal options. We're a casual eatery that is excited to bring something new to the Toronto food scene, and we would love for you to come join us soon!

post_title: Como en Casa, Fresh Mexican Kitchen - Toronto
post_content:
Como en Casa, Fresh Mexican Kitchen is a restaurant located in the Downtown Area, at Yonge and Wellesley. Our specialties are some of the best known dishes from Mexico, with a fresh and healthy touch. We offer affordable prices, home-made food, quick service. Eat in and take out orders in a total fast casual atmosphere! 
 
Our menu offers standard Mexican dishes like Tacos, Burritos and Quesadillas. We add a mosaic of flavours to a traditional Mexican grill, some other Latinamerican especialities like Empanadas and a variety of traditional Guisados (Stews).
 
Como en Casa Fresh Mexican Kitchen is located on the northeast side of Yonge St. at Wellesley in downtown Toronto. We are located steps away from Wellesley Sbw Station.

post_content:
Find our food in four bars in the neighborhood: Aspetta, The Embassy Bar, Ronnie’s Local 069, and Cold Tea. Stop by and listen to the Beatles with us while you eat in the heart of Kensington Market!

We were voted best poutine and best fish and chips in Toronto!

Try our crispy and delicious fish. Fish, Chips and Poutines are our specialties. The goal at Fresco's Fish & Chips is to serve the best fish and chips: good for you, good for the environment and really, really good to eat. Before opening the restaurant we personally tested everything before doing market research and development on all of our dishes. We tested 300 pounds of potatoes before deciding on the ones we use. We use fresh Ontario grown Russet potatoes which are freshly cut daily. We inspect each potato individually before cutting them, and rinse the cut potatoes 3 times before we blanch them, assuring the best quality and best tasting fries you will ever have.  We use only the best fish, chosen for its consistent excellence. Some of our fish are Ocean Wise sustainable seafood products.

Since April 2010

post_content: Calling all pierogi lovers, your dreams have just come true! This October chefs Bryan Burke and Adam Dolley are launching a new restaurant concept called "Loaded Pierogi". Their dishes are not to be mistaken for your Bubbie's pierogi, this venture is all about the toppings. Starting with a great base handmade pierogi either cooked classic or crispy, filled with potato and cheddar topped with everything you could ever want from duck confit, pulled pork, fried brussel sprouts, lobster, kimchi...there is something for every palate. Let the countdown begin. Cheers!

post_content:
Marben Restaurant is in the heart of King West, just off the beaten path.  The space was originally designed by a collective of local artists and has more recently been rejuvenated through the joined forces of our proprietor, Simon Benstead alongside Bradley Denton of Pencil Design.  Its a space that caters to anyone and everyone whether you're looking for a celebratory dinner, burgers and beers or late-night cocktails and snacks.  Our menu is focused on seasonality. With an honest approach to cuisine, it's home cooking, executed at a very high level. We are fortunate to be able to offer a gorgeous private event space that is designed to cater to birthdays, weddings, business receptions and presentations of any kind.

Marben's beverage program focuses on wines that reflect our food and pair well with the well rounded nature of our offerings.  A serious but fun approach to the timeless classics encourage our guests to have that perfectly executed cocktail, every time. 

Come see what's tucked away on Wellington St West. We would love for you to be our guest.

post_content:
Tu Casa
Nestled deep in the heart of Lorne Park among the prestigious homes and
manicured lawns is a welcoming home of another name, Tu Casa. 

We officially opened our doors July 20th 2009. Tu Casa, provides a truly unique atmosphere for patrons in search of an authentic, classic,
fine-dining experience.

Tu Casa’s design is an open format, display kitchen and full service bar, creating
a high-energy social destination inviting to a wide range of guests, including groups,
couples, families and business people. Our sophisticated menus and daily specials
appeal to lunch and dinner guests, as well as those who want to enjoy our half priced
bar appetizers from 3PM to 6 PM. Our wide-ranging appeal and premium location
attract a highly desirable guest demographic.
Our food is a fusion of the finest classical ingredients, resulting in a purity of taste that
transcends fads and truly excites patrons’ palates. Our Mediterranean and Continental
menu reflects a hint of classical cuisine with a twist of innovative flair. 

To compliment our menu is an extensive wine list with over 240 different international
wines with a growing selection of superb wines from Ontario and the rest of Canada.
We maintain our wines at the perfect serving temperature in our climate controlled 
redwood wine cellar. Wines by the glass include premium wines served from our 
Enomatic wine system, guaranteeing freshness with every glass.

Tu Casa presents a tasteful, sophisticated ambiance that flows from our intimate patio
to our private solarium and continues throughout our main dining room. 

Tu Casa is a perfect destination for a business lunch, social gathering or a romantic dinner.
Tu Casa…  Welcome Home

The flavour of Saravana Bhavan is renowned not only in Chennai, India but all over the world. This premier chain of restaurants has been delighting millions of customers for over 25 years, through its 48 outlets in India, USA, UK, UAE, Oman, Singapore and Malaysia.

Now you can enjoy the same rich quality, right here in Canada (Mississauga, and Scarborough). Hotel Saravanaa Bhavan (HSB) is a contemporary style family restaurant serving authentic, high quality vegetarian food, using the finest quality ingredients.

At HSB, we take pride in providing each guest with a genuine South Indian dining experience. Personal, attentive service is combined with uniformly excellent, exceptional tasty and always fresh food. The atmosphere is bright and lively, the prices moderate, the service quick and the staff friendly. The restaurant seats upwards of 75 people, and features spacious, elegant surroundings, with ambient, classical South Indian music humming in the background. Our efficient & gracious staff awaits the pleasure of serving you.

Who we are.

Once upon a time, our family decided to buy a bar. As lovers of craft beer and a good challenge, we jumped at the opportunity to create a local space where the community could just kick back with a brew. The Grover has been a local institution since 1982, and with its recent rebirth, lives on as a favourite community hub. Expect perfectly poured "brewtiful" craft pints, damn good pub fare, awesome staff, and fabulous events :)

The Grover.

Everyone needs that "third space", a place that isn't work and isn't home. Where neighbours congregate and Ontario craft beer flows. Your pint is waiting.

post_content:
Fresh and local pub fare done right.

The menu great selections such as beer-battered fish and chips,  bangers and mash, as well as classic pub fare such as Pork Side Ribs, House made burgers, nachos and savoury chicken sandwiches and wraps and of course all-day breakfast is available on our menu. Nice touches like tea and coffee being served with a made in-house shortbread cookie that add to the homey friendliness. 

All of the desserts are also baked in-house with the sticky toffee pudding already being raved about in the neighborhood. On the side - Piper's offers 10 draught taps and choice single malt whiskeys at very reasonable prices. The menu is sure to satisfy everyone's cravings and even the little ones have their own menu! Piper's welcomes tea and coffee social groups as well as dart clubs, large parties and teams! With our late hours and scheduled live entertainment, there's always a reason to drop in and you will always be made to feel very welcome. Piper's Pub and Grill has become a favourite hotspot for locals.
 
Established in our minds 1966.

Riverdale's best kept secret is an eco-cafe called The Social Gardener, providing a working model of change that is responding to emerging social and environmental issues with community economic development and civic co-operation. 

The Social Gardener Cafe invites the public into the entire building, the Riverdale Hub; home to an immigrant women's centre, open concept/private work spaces, meeting rooms, event space, recreational studio, copy centre, community kitchen, rainwater garden, rooftop garden; all which runs under a 90% energy efficient model. This becomes a playground to plant ideas and grow meaningful work.

Phone. 647-925-3094
Address. 1326 Gerrard St. East, Toronto, ON, M4L 1Z1

post_content: There is a growing movement towards healthy, plant-based diets, and an understanding that meat, dairy and eggs are unnecessary.  At the same time there is a maturing of our society towards an ethical awareness of the horrors of factory farming and the unsustainability of animal husbandry in general.  I do not aim to convince you of this movement or of the mounting evidence.  I am a vegan facilitator, eager to find those who have already determined to start down the road to veganism, or have started and are needing some help and encouragement through shopping, cooking and social adaptations.

post_content:
TWIST by Roger Mooking

Whether it's a light snack & beverage before your boarding time or a longer lip smacking & satisfying sit down meal before your flight, dinning at Pearson International Airport never tasted so good. 

Chef Roger Mooking, Food Network Celebrity Chef, TV Host and Award Winning Cookbook Author has created a menu at Twist that focuses on North American comfort foods with a global Twist. Chef Mooking has always had an infinity for global cuisine. Born in Trinidad with Caribbean/ Chinese heritage and being raised in Canada, Roger is no stranger to international influences in cooking. 

Working with local vendors, freshness and quality ingredients are top of mind when it comes to Chef Mooking's international yet approachable menu. 

Make sure to stop by this award winning chef's restaurant in Terminal 1 next time you fly!

Final Description:
We opened April 1, 2011 and have been having fun every day since, right in the heart of Toronto's financial district.  We have loved meeting new customers every day while getting to know our loyal regulars.

The team at Prairie Girl is proud of our incredible cupcakes! We LOVE to talk about how they are made fresh on-site every single day from fresh dairy butter, 70% Dark Belgian Chocolate, real strawberries and tons of other top of the line ingredients!

November 14, 2011 we opened up our second location in the Path.  Located in the concourse level of First Canadian Place, we deliver the same great product, but available at 8am for those early risers, and wonderfully convenient as the cold approaches.

April 26, 2013 We opened our third location in the trendy neighbourhood of Yorkville! Now our cupcakes are conveniently available uptown still served with a smile! 

Because of our commitment to "fresh" each of our stores has it's own kitchen where our favourite products are baked everyday. This means that sometimes we sell out early due to a higher demand than expected. This also means some days we have leftovers and because of our love and dedication to the community in which we work, we give our end-of-day cupcakes to a couple of Second Harvest agencies nearby our stores.

Stay connected with Prairie Girl and you'll get chances to take part in contests and giveaways all the time! :)

Many great vegan and gluten-free cupcakes and other baked goods.

post_content:
** CLOSED | RE-OPENING WINTER 2018 **

The spirit of the fall season symbolizing change has presented us with an opportunity to evolve our space of gatherings at Alternity, and reveal a sense that we have out-grown our location at Christie St. We're sad to announce that we left a spot that nurtured the birth of our events venue, but more so excited about the future unveiling in our path to greater potential.

As of November 1st, Alternity on Christie St is closed and will be opening early in 2018 in a new location! We're excited to share the details of what's in store for our evolution and will post another update as soon as we have news to share!

We'd like to thank everyone that was part of creating so many special memories at Alternity. All your continued support has fueled our inspiration to continue this journey together, towards more enchanting moments, cherishing a 'shared experience' with another...

Six Raw Juice Company is a proud Toronto based vegan restaurant that offers cold-pressed juice. The Six first opened up it’s doors in September 2015 and has two locations. 
At The Six, we mean what we claim. We are committed to providing only the best and freshest products on the market, and combining them into nutritional and delicious treats and beverages. Using organic ingredients that are locally grown by our very own Ontario farmers, we provide great diet choices for vegans, health conscience individuals, or anyone looking to enrich their mind and body with healthy food options! What is our promise to you? Our juices are never pasteurized, put under high pressure processing, or put in to plastic bottles. Using the power of customer service, we help you fulfill your health and lifestyle goals with the help of high quality and delicious foods and beverages.
Not only are our products healthy and tasty, but they cannot be found anywhere else. Our unique blends and juices have a variety of different flavours that provide a plethora of health benefits. Check us out at: http://www.lovethesix.com/

post_content:
Fiesta Farms is Toronto’s largest inde­pen­dently owned gro­cery store and gar­den cen­tre. What does that mean? It means we only have one store. But it’s a big one. “Largest” means we carry the range of prod­ucts you’d expect from a chain. “Independent” means we can choose what those prod­ucts are-who makes them, where they come from, what’s in them, their place in the local econ­omy. Stuff like that.

And we’re pretty choosy.

Partly because being choosy is good, and partly because it’s good busi­ness. When we opened up over 20 years ago, we decided to focus on two things the big guys couldn’t com­pete with: serv­ing our local eth­nic com­mu­ni­ties and sup­port­ing our local econ­omy. Now those things are pop­u­lar. And so are we!

A visit to the store will let you know pretty quickly that we don’t turn our nose up at any­one, but we tend to be par­tic­u­larly pop­u­lar with folks who get more from food shop­ping than just a full larder. As it turns out, food mat­ters to a lot of peo­ple for a lot of dif­fer­ent reasons.

We help them cel­e­brate those rea­sons by mak­ing organic, local, eth­i­cal, eth­nic, healthy, gourmet, arti­san and tra­di­tional fare acces­si­ble. We’ve got lots of it. We keep the prices for it all rea­son­able. And we sell it with­out the pomp. We wouldn’t know how to pull off pomp if the Queen were com­ing to pick up a Fenwood Farms chicken.

What we  can pull off are part­ner­ships with great orga­ni­za­tions like Local Food Plus, who under­stand the impor­tance of devel­op­ing and pro­mot­ing local entre­pre­neurs to our econ­omy and our envi­ron­ment. And orga­ni­za­tions like The Stop and The New Farm, who help peo­ple exer­cise their right to good food, whether they can afford it or not.

Long story short? We’re a nice gro­cery store and gar­den cen­tre with good stuff.

post_content: The West End Food Co-op is a non-profit multistakeholder food co-op. The co-op is committed to bringing more healthy and culturally appropriate food to the West End, and creating a hub for food change. The Co-op responds to the needs of all stakeholders in the local food system, and seeks solutions to shared problems. Owner-member groups include farmers, consumers, workers, and community partners. Activities include a weekly farmers market, community food programming and the development of a community owned store. The Co-op combines the creation of new markets that link producers, food artisans and consumers with community-based job creation and community food programming and education.

post_title: Through Being Cool Vegan Baking Co.
post_content:
TBC is a strictly vegan bake shop/grocery. 100% vegan, 100% of the time. Everything is made in house.
We have a large variety of grocery items including take home frozen meals like cabbage rolls, pot pies, breakfast burritos and enchiladas. Also, take a look in our fridge for favourites like mac and cheeze, eggy tofu salad, pizza dough, marinated seitan, soyrizo and a selection of mayos and sauces.
We also carry a variety of condiments, preserves and pickles that we can ourselves. 
Sandwiches are available everyday after 11 with a listed menu as well as rotating specials! Our sandwiches are 100% made by us-from the bread to every topping.
We use organic and local ingredients whenever possible.
TBC proudly serves Anchored Coffee both in espresso and cold brewed form, and also make our own syrups for specialty lattes and sodas. We carry a selection of Herbal Infusions Teas that can be hot or iced.

post_title: The Fix + Co. Plant Based Kitchen and Catering
post_content:
Find Your Fix!

The Fix and Co provides fresh pressed juices, salad bowls and other freshly made goods in the Six and surrounding areas.

The Fix + Co was created in 2015 by two girls who have a passion for educating the community on healthy eating. Their mission is to provide high quality, nutritious and convenient meals to customers by delivery.  The Fix emerged out of a belief that today’s consumers are becoming more enlightened about the detrimental effects of eating typical convenience junk foods that are highly processed, with little to no nutritional value. Today’s consumer is becoming more health conscious and wants to take back their right to choose healthy and nutritiously dense foods that will benefit their overall well-being. The consumer wants to know where their food is coming from and what their meals are made of. This is where The Fix comes in. The Fix believes that educating the community on healthy eating is the first step to achieving a healthy, fulfilled lifestyle. 

#thefixinthesix #thefix

post_content:
Our food is inspired and prepared according to the Ontario growing season, so our market menu changes depending on what is available from our local farmers. We use all vegan and mainly raw ingredients and choose organic wherever possible.

We offer a savoury menu full of fresh, plant-based produce from various Ontario farms, seasoned and spiced with bright, rich flavors. Our sweet menu consists of raw nuts, seeds, fresh and dried fruits and natural sweeteners such as agave nectar, maple syrup and honey. Our drink menu is made up of smoothies, fresh juices, and lemonades.

We dehydrate, blend, chop, grate, soak, roast, boil, sprout and mix our ingredients, all of which add to the variety and uniqueness of our food. Above all, we aspire to make simply delicious and healthful food, the same kind of food we love to eat and enjoy.

post_content:
We've taken the Bull by the horns, opening  the doors of our very first store on September 2011 at 179 Parliament Street  in  Downtown Toronto, Ontario,  No Bull  Burgers is  bringing  the art of burger making  back to the  basics. 


Uniquely paired with local Ontario farms bringing you the freshest, certified organic extra lean beef.  All of our burgers are lightly spiced and ground fresh daily with no additives, preservatives or fillers.   We only cook our burgers "to order" on a traditional flat top griddle to maintain taste, consistency and flavour.  Here at No Bull Burgers, we don't tell you how to order, with dozens of FREE premium toppings and sauces every burger is made exactly theway you want it….........No Bull.   There are hundreds of burger combinations from pickles to pineapple, from tomatoes to tzatziki.  It doesn't stop there..
We're serious about our sides, we only serve fresh cut fries made with 100% yukon gold potatoes. Upgrade to our montreal style poutine wiTh real cheese curds, or try our exclusive homemade No Bull chips spiced up the way you like 'em.

Raw Aura was established August 2009, founded on the principle of balance, and fuelled by a passion for healthy homemade cuisine without having to compromise on flavour!

Over the years, we’ve stayed true to our roots, offering delicious *living food, drink and dessert options that satisfy all palettes.

All of our meals, drinks and desserts are made from scratch, using only the finest ingredients, whether they be locally sourced, organic or both, and our fair is entirely vegan, gluten and sugar free, which enables people with specific dietary restrictions the opportunity to order freely off our menu. 

Our tasty food options, alongside a positive and inclusive restaurant setting, has afforded us the opportunity to bridge the gap between people with different nutritional values, which is something we are truly grateful for. 

We are thankful to all of our customers, and look forward to many more years of sustainability!

This historic landmark, is set to become one of Toronto’s most exciting and relevant downtown destinations. Here you will enjoy the ambiance, charm and culinary delights of Toronto’s newest and finest eateries.

Tastes of Market Street is an inspired and unique urban historic restoration project that will rejuvenate the St. Lawrence Market neighbourhood. Seven unique and charming restaurants, cafes and stores with outdoor patios, will connect Front Street to The Esplanade across from the western Side of St. Lawrence Market.

Feast on Coconut Calamari, Lamb Tikka and Butter Chicken at Bindia, sip on specialty Sangria’s and relish Tapas at Barsa Taberna, savour lobster rolls and fish tacos at Market Street Catch, choose from some of the world’s finest olive oils and spices from Olive and Olives, watch the world go by while sipping fresh roasted coffee from Balzac’s, delve in to delicious Italian comfort food at Pastizza and enjoy healthy and tasty organic, fresh foods that inspire and nourish at Evolution Food Co.

post_content:
WHO IS EVA?

Eva is the grandmother of co-owner Justin Butler. She was born and raised in Budapest, Hungary and travelled to Canada with her children during the Hungarian Revolution of the 1950s. Family trips to Budapest eating Kürtőskalács (Chimneys) are the inspiration for Eva's Original Chimneys.

WHAT'S A CHIMNEY?

Known as Kürtöskalács in Hungarian, Chimney cakes are delicious and unique freshly baked Hungarian pastries, named after their hollow, cylindrical shape.

EVA'S INGREDIENTS

Our Chimney Cakes and Cones are cooked using a traditional-style rotisserie grill and are baked, not fried.

The dough base is suitable for vegans and our staff can advise on what toppings are suitable for vegans, too.

The base ingredients of each Chimney are: unbleached flour, organic coconut milk, organic cane sugar, sunflower oil, lemon, fresh yeast and sea salt.

We work with a local baker, Val of Sweet Carnival Cakes, to make our delicious toppings from scratch using premium ingredients.  

OUR CASHLESS POLICY

It’s not that we don’t want your cash ;)  But, Eva’s is operating with electronic payments only so we can be faster, more hygienic and more accurate for everyone! Hygiene is particularly important to us as our entire kitchen is out front where the register is.

We believe this is the future of payment and we thank you for joining us as we make this step!

post_content:
After winning best bakery in the city for 2014, we've decided to expand and Innovate! Opening in 2015, Toronto's first vegan Pizza Shop & Snack Bar!

What's a snack bar? That's the real beautiful part of this whole thing--it's basically your vegan junk food dreams come alive. Vegan Corn Dogs... Vegan Doughnuts... Vegan Cheezy Garlic Bread... Buffalo Ranch Salads and Vegan Not-Chicken Caesar Salads. 

Our pizzas are done in an authentic pizza oven that never even one time has had meat in it. Also aren't you tired of omnivores just sprinkling some Daiya on some crust and calling it vegan pizza? We 1) know how to make vegan cheese taste like the real thing 2) we make our own mock meat and we know how to cook it so it doesn't taste like a mummy's fingers 3) We understand how wholly sick you are or just eating tomato sauce and veggies. 

For too long Toronto has envied all those American cities with real vegan toppings and more than one vegan sauce base, and dip... remember GARLIC DIP? We do. And we got you. We have 6 kinds of dip. And you can eat all of it. 

Fool your friends! P00n your hockey team by making them eat vegetarian and totally not know! Maybe die at a slightly slower rate because you didn't eat bacon today! Just come get some authentically vegan, not passably vegan pizza and stuff it in your cool beautiful faces. 

Established 2014.

Winner of Toronto Best Bakery 2014, Now Magazine Readers Choice; Toronto Life Magazine Best of the Neighbourhood 2014 - Christie; Winner of the Toronto Vegetarian Association Best New Vegetarian/Vegan Restaurant 2015. 

Featured on: CBC Radio 1 - Ontario Today, Why Do Vegetarians Bother With Fake Meat; The Toronto Star - Food and Lifestyle - Making the Pig Destroyer Destroyer for Sourced; Now Magazine, January 2015 - Mac and Cheese Issue; Toronto Life Magazine 2014; Globe and Mail February 2015 - Food and Lifestyle Section; Cooking Channel USA, Food Network Canada - Sugar Showdown S1, E7 - Garden Pies.

Beaches Bakeshop & Cafe' is a little cozy cafe in the heart of "Upper Beaches"! Located in Kingston Road Village. First you see the Swedish Flag and then you enter and let the atmosphere hit you. We are a bit of a hub for Scandinavians in Toronto. On the shelves you will find Swedish Cookbooks. Some to borrow while you sit in and some available to purchase. Everything we serve is made on the premises, homemade soups with no dairy or wheat. Healthy and filling salads, Quinoa, Red Rice, Black Beans, Sweet Potatoes, Cabbage and Kale are just a few of the staples we cook with on a daily basis. Vegetarian options always available!
We bake "in Swedish". Mazariner, Dammsugare and Sarah Bernards sit side by side in the pastry case! Marabou, Fazer, Cloetta and many more are brands we carry!

post_content:
California Sandwiches was born in Toronto’s Little Italy. During the mid 
1960’s, the Papa/Bertucci family purchased a local grocery store with 
the hope of supporting a growing family. They quickly discovered they 
had something special when customers were coming for lunch instead 
of groceries. As the popularity of their homemade sandwiches grew, they 
decided to jump on the opportunity. In 1967 the first California Sandwiches 
was born. From its inception as “La Rinacente”, the veal sandwich quickly 
became one of Toronto’s favorites.
Today, very little has changed. There are now 12 locations, all family 
owned and operated. Traditional methods of food preparation are still in 
practice. Each store has its own butcher and the meat is cut on site. Only 
the finest in Italian tomatoes are ground for our sauce that is made fresh 
daily. Our kaiser buns are baked by an Italian bakery and delivered every 
morning. And our cheeses and produce are bought and prepared for use 
as needed. Quality food and attention to detail have kept this business 
strong and valued.

Chopan Grill is a chain of family owned Afghan restaurants that have been in business since early 1980s in multiple locations within the United States of America. On July 23rd 2013 Chopan Grill opened its first location in Mississauga, Ontario, Canada to serve Authentic cuisine from Afghanistan and India to its Canadian customers.

Chopan Grill serves large varieties of grilled meat including Chicken, Beef, Lamb and Seafood. It also serves special Afghan steamed dumplings (Mantoo), boiled dumplings (Aushak), Afghan noodles, several rice dishes, curries and many more. 

Its Indian menu includes some popular dishes such as Butter Chicken, Chicken Tikka Masala, Daal Makhni, Alo Gobhi and Tandoori Chicken.

It is worth mentioning that Chopan Grill also serves some delicious vegetarian dishes such as Sabzi Chalow (Spinach with white rice), sweet pumpkin, lentils, okra, kidney beans, Sambosa, Boolani and egg plant.

In addition to its dine in and take out services, Chopan Grill also provides catering services in premises and off premises.

post_content:
The year was 1987; it was a warm spring day in the month of May when Stanley Rampersaud proudly opened the doors of the very first Calypso Hut Restaurant. It specialized in the finest Guyanese Style Chinese cuisine that was relatively unknown in the city of Toronto. 

Hard work, determination and generosity were the key ingredients to making this dream an overnight success. And the success continues, 26 years later and Calypso Hut (and also Hut Like Pepper, its sister restaurant) is widely known throughout Ontario and loved by many. 

How do we do it, you ask? Simple. Provide quality food, outstanding customer service and affordable prices. Years later, and we still see many of our very first customers who have shared their love of our food with their children and grandchildren. Come see for yourself, we're open 7 days a week

post_content:
INDIAN HALF PLATES & FULL DRINKS

Our Story

We have taken the name Leela from the play /theatre Ram-Leela. Leela is a dramatic folk re-enactment of the life of Lord Rama, ending up in ten-day battle between Rama and Ravana, as described in the Hindu religious epic, the Ramayana. A tradition that originates from the Indian-subcontinent, the play is staged annually, often over ten or more successive nights, during the auspicious period of Navratras which marks the commencement of the Autumn festive period, starting with the Dussehra festival. Usually the performances are timed to culminate on the festival day, that commemorates the victory of Rama over demon king Ravana, when the actors are taken out in a procession through the city, leading up to a mela (fairground) ground or town square, where the enactment of the final battle takes place, before giant effigies of Ravana, his brother Kumbhakaran and son Meghanath are set on fire and coronation of Rama at Ayodhaya takes place, marking the culmination of festivities and restoration of the divine order.

The Food

With the opening of Leela, Hemant brings the flavours of his home country stateside, showcasing his Indian heritage through Canadian ingredients. The food at Leela covers all regions of India, and celebrates the wonders of Indian ‘Dhaba’ (road-side eatery in every neighbourhood or highways) food along with lesser-known dishes. The portions are all tapas style.

 Tasting Menu

The most important part of the menu is the Banana Leaf Tasting Menu - A tasting menu with most delicious colonial Indian dishes. All served in small bowls and usually on a fresh banana leaf. At the time India was a Brit Colony, people used to show off their wealth by serving in silver platters. Our fun menu does a spoof on those platters and we serve on fresh banana leaf.

Cross-Over Interpretation of Indian 

Some will argue that cross-over interpretation of Indian street food comes at a cost of authenticity but Hemant Bhagwani disagrees. He believes that we need to revolutionize Indian food to represent its accomplishments and diversity on foreign shores, to be able to innovate you have to go back to tradition. It’s about adapting your food to local cultures and palates and at the same time reviving old forgotten Indian street food dishes by giving them a fun makeover to attract the attention it deserves. “with one foot in future and one in past, the menu at Leela reads a romantic fairy tale of “desi khana” marrying innovative Indian Food.

post_content:
Leslie Jones says...
Enjoy our Winter Special! Wednesdays to Saturdays from 5:00pm to 6:00pm, all pizzas are $7 with the purchase of a beverage!

Leslie Jones is a Leslieville hotspot where you find quality food in a cozy atmosphere. Chef George Wensley welcomes you into his home away from home where you will find an ever changing menu of the best local fare and his favourite vinyl spinning on the hi-fi. This is the type of place that quickly finds a spot on your list of favourite restaurants due in no small part to the wonderful staff, reasonably priced menu and why NOW magazine named them one of the top 10 restaurants in 2006.

A focus on using the best locally sourced ingredients results in raves for dishes such as the Jerk Pulled Pork with Fresh Mango Salsa and Chili mayo, Roasted Duck with Fennel in a Fresh Herb pastry and a taste of yesterday with a traditional Carrot Cake.

The charm of the neighbourhood's many artists and vintage shops is carried on at Leslie Jones. A rotating gallery of artists decorate the walls of the small space showing off the talent of our home-grown artists. The lush patio out back is a welcome get-away from the hustle and bustle of Queen St and a lovely spot to enjoy a beautiful Toronto summer night.

Located at Jane & Finch Mall, Living Well is a family owned restaurant and has been serving the community for over 5 years. With the business carried through the hardships and successes by the Grace of God.

Serving you great food at a great price! Meals starting at $3.50 (2pc chicken with rice and sauce). We have "Toonie Tuesdays" every... well, Tuesdays! For $2.75, you get 2pc fried chicken with rice and sauce.

Our most popular meal consists of select 3 size chicken meals. Mini $3.50 (Small), Medium $5, and Mega $7 (Large). A choice of Fried, BBQ, or Jerk. A choice of Rice & Peas, Steamed Rice or & Fried Rice. And a choice of sauce on your food, Jerk & Red sauce, Curry Goat, Oxtail, Curry, Stew Chicken and/or Fish gravy!

Other selections on our menu includes Stew Chicken, Curry Chicken, Curry Goat, and Oxtail. All comes with your choice of rice. We also have seafood made as you order them. It takes about 10 minutes to prepare. Steamed Fish, Brown Stew Fish, Curry Shrimps, and Plain Shrimps. Served with steamed vegetables and your choice of rice. We also serve Fried Snappers.

Like finger foods? We serve dumplings and beef patties!

If you're around the area and craving for some Caribbean food, jerk, oxtail, curry goat, please drop by and let us serve you.

post_content:
The renowned Mitzi’s Café can be found tucked away in residential Roncesvalles Village. Newly renovated and rebranded, Mitzi’s brings a fresh take on the “all-day brunch spot,” whilst staying true to the neighbourhood’s heritage.
 
 True to Mitzi’s form, the menu includes favourites such as thick, fluffy omelettes, challah French toast and golden buttermilk oatmeal pancakes, all of which are crafted in the open-air kitchen.

 We are proud to have a loyal following at Mitzi’s who come for our delicious homemade food and of course always welcome first-timers to come and sample our unique creations.

 A typical brunch might feature poached egg topped with lobster sauce, so you see we like to do things a little differently around here! Our dishes are not only homemade, but are seasonally relevant and come from local distributors. In addition, we offer a range of vegetarian, specialty and gluten-free options.

 Whether you prefer an early morning breakfast with friends or relaxing on a sunny afternoon with a latte, Mitzi’s provides the perfect mix between friendly neighbourhood atmosphere and relaxed chill-out spot.

post_content:
Hyderabadi cuisine known as 'Deccan' cuisine of

India, refers to the culinary practices of the South

Indian city of Hyderabad. The cuisine consists of a

broad repertoire of rice, wheat, and meat dishes,

which are carefully prepared using a unique blend

of spices, herbs, and natural edibles.

 

Unlike North Indian cuisine, Hyderabadi cuisine is

characterized by the extensive use of coconut,

tamarind, peanuts, and sesame seeds during the

slow cooking process. Slow cooking is the hallmark

of Hyderabadi cuisine and all items are prepared in traditional way.

 

At Saffron Foods, our mission is to prepare 100% ethnic Hyderabadi food using the slow cooking technique and the right combination of spices, all of which are prepared in house.

 

We welcome you to visit Saffron Foods - your gateway to Hyderabadi cuisine

At Saffron Foods, our mission is to prepare 100% ethnic Hyderabadi food using the slow cooking technique and the right combination of spices, all of which are prepared in house.

 

We welcome you to visit Saffron Foods - your gateway to Hyderabadi cuisine

post_content:
In 1985 our founder, Angelo Christou, opened Sunset Grill's doors for the first time in the Beaches area of Toronto, Ontario. Armed with the basic info that Fresh is Tastiest™, Sunset Grill quickly developed long lineups of loyal customers. With huge popularity and consistent service, it quickly became the place to be for the best breakfast in town.
It is said that when something works, don’t change it. After more than 30 years in business, we realize that while the world around us has evolved, our concept and methods have not changed. After all, good food, fast service and a pleasant experience is what a successful restaurant is all about.
Our food and preparation methods are 5 star inspired and quality is never sacrificed. All our menu items are cooked fresh to order using healthy methods: flat top grills, pat dry bacon and nothing is ever deep fried. With choices such as our famous bacon and 3 eggs for breakfast or our flagship Sunset Burgers for lunch, we invite you try our restaurants for an experience you can count on!

Food is comfort. We make it easy for you to enjoy a delicious meal without even leaving the hotel. Whether you are into health food, snacks, or gourmet food all the way, we’ve got something to tickle your palate. Stay in and use our in-room dining service, check out the onsite restaurant, or unwind with after-dinner drinks at the bar.

Opening its second location in Mississauga, at the TAZA Grill + Bar you may surround yourself in a warm ambiance for both social and intimate dinners. Our floor-to-ceiling windows showcase an unobstructed view of our serene private Garden Courtyard. Whether you are in the mood for a quiet fireside table or want to catch the latest sporting event on one of our big screen TVs, the award winning TAZA Grill + Bar is the perfect place to spend your evening. Adjacent to our TAZA Restaurant is our outdoor patio, Relax in our private Garden Courtyard while enjoying a delicious meal or refreshing drink. We, at the DoubleTree by Hilton Hotel Toronto Airport West, are honoured to have our very own TAZA Grill + Bar be recognized and voted one of the top five hotel Restaurants in Mississauga.
