post_content:
Taste of Jaffna is a newly formed Sri-Lankan restaurant situated in the Scarborough community and nearby the intersection of Markham and Ellesmere. We offer a wide range of authentic Sri-Lankan food and are committed to delivering the same degree of food quality you would expect in a home cooked meal. 

Our experienced cooks specialize in popular items such as our mouth-watering kothu roti and biryani as well as a number of tasty sweets and short eats. 

We also love the challenge of creating specialty orders of certain sweets and delicacies for special events.

What sets Taste of Jaffna apart is our attention to detail and our desire for superior taste in each and every dish we create. 
Come by and see for yourself how we have recreated the taste of our homeland right here in Toronto!

post_content:
Taste of Tunisia the only Tunisian restaurant in Toronto. Originally established in 2004 under Djerba La Douce it changed ownership in 2011 and was renamed Taste of Tunisia. Taste of Tunisia offers a unique warm and authentic Tunisian dining experience (Authentic Tunisian Food and a freindly and welcoming hospitality). Our food is 100% Fresh, 100% Halal.

At taste of Tunisia we do not just serve tunisian food, we a are more than that, we welcome you like we welcome our house guests, we treat you like we treat our house guests and we ensure you enjoy the time you spend at our restaurant like we make our guests at ease at home, after all, this is just what the Tunisian Hospitality is all about. Come visit us and judge by yourself… 

Our restaurant is a small & intimate restaurant and whether dropping by for a quick meal, a night out with friends, a family outing or celebrating a great occasion, Taste of Tunisia has what you are looking for.

With our main dining room, a beautiful back patio and a private function room, we welcome your private functions, whether for a meeting, a birthday or a large group gathering, we will be delighted to add a Tunisian flavour to your event.

The Pie Commission serves handmade savoury (and some sweet) 5" pies, born and baked in Toronto! 
We offer a modern interpretation of the classic British-style savoury pie. 
We make all of our pies from scratch, in-house, using only natural ingredients with nothing weird, that-you-can’t-pronounce added. This includes only premium cuts of Canadian meat, the freshest produce and homemade beef, chicken and vegetable stocks, all enveloped in a dangerously delicious all-butter crust.  

The savoury pie has been reinvented.  

Pies served baked hot or frozen and hot pies can be served with fresh handcut Fries, Mixed Green Salad or Coleslaw.

BLOODY GOOD PIES!

post_content:
Escape to PARALIA 

Experience first hand the importance Greeks place on ‘filoxenia’- the taking of a stranger in the middle of the night when he did not expect it, to share everything without question.

Watch as our kitchen teams carve the towering mountain of ice that beds the ‘catch-of-the-day’ flown in directly from the Mediteranean and the Agean Sea.

They say that for Greeks life begins at midnight. The bar at Paralia is no exception. Representing a Greece of ‘today’, the bar at Paralia is abuzz with ouzo fueled conversation fused with an eclectic pulse of groove tempo beats.

Built to resemble a Greek monastery, you will likely find on the island of Santorini or Crete. Paralia which is overlooking the beach as well as being accompanied by one of the most exclusive views in Toronto, is where mezzedes makes friends out of strangers and the event of the main course welcomes all as family.

post_content:
From the design to the décor to the menu, Tundra was conceived to evoke the image, the texture and the taste of Canada.

Now celebrating 15 delicious years, Tundra remains true to its original concept … Canadian inspired cuisine.  Under the tutelage of Toronto native, Kevin Prendergast, our culinary brigade offers a wealth of cooking techniques and styles, thanks to their multicultural and ethnically diverse backgrounds. 

Inspired by fresh, locally sourced produce and protein, sustainable seafood and foraged gems from independent purveyors, our team passionately makes each dining experience unique … depending on the season and the ingredients.

The wine list is well sourced offering variety in by the glass, on tap, bottle and vintage selections.  Canadian craft beer and cocktails that are both classic, yet original are always available. 

Tundra is elegant and stylish, yet relaxed and welcoming with warm, excellent service and always an enchanting experience.  It is conveniently located in the heart of the city at Richmond and University Avenue, within the contemporary  Hilton Toronto hotel.  

Open for breakfast, lunch and dinner with well tailored menus for all dining experiences from power breakfasts to pre-theatre prix fixe menus to corporate, casual or formal events.

Harpers Landing Bar Grill Hub, is a North American bistro, broad and egalitarian in scope. The Harpers Landing menu is accessible & wide-ranging, the ingredients proudly fresh and whenever possible sustainable, local and organic. The dishes are crafted by our very authentic, well-traveled & passionate Italian chef, Marco D’Angelo. The bar provides a wide-reaching variety of sophisticated products and the wine list is deep, considerately priced and offers an extremely satisfying number of wines by the glass.
Harpers Landing Bar Grill Hub, as the name suggests, lends itself to many occasions. Lunch & dinner, seven days a week, weekend brunch, a snack, a beverage, a celebration, a business occasion, a dodge on a sunny patio day. Tether your dog to the patio fence & enjoy a glass of wine. Patio seats 160, indoors 226, the bar, an additional 35. We have the ability to host group events. Small groups privately, larger groups in a semi-private fashion.
